div.p:
He cannot reuerence him in his heart, he cannot but yeelde

 that the ſaying of the holy Ghoſt is true, that a focle in a day is knowne by his wrath, You can hardly find a fooles heart without ſome coales of fretting and anger. And theſe be the means to kepe one from this firſt inward breach of this cōmandement; 
                     Ʋiz. carnall, fleſhly and ſenſuall anger, that comes from the diuell, hardens our brothers heart more, and hinders our ſelues from doing the good that elſe we might.
